race.comment: CAMPARI TWIST (2) is a lightly raced mare back from a brief spell. Progressed nicely last prep, finishing second at Echuca at her latest outing over 1200m in a BM64. Going well at the jump-outs and looks ready to fire. AREYOUREADYFORIT (9) returned from an eight-week break with a pleasing run at Bendigo then ventured to Adelaide last start and got too far back to be competitive in a 1200m BM62 for mares. Drawn to travel closer today and can improve coming back a little in grade. MEISHO (13) raced on the speed and gave a kick but was beaten narrowly over 1110m at Kilmore last time. Gets her chance in what looks a slightly easier assignment. GEMINGA (3) returns from a five-month break. Started favourite at Morphettville first-up last prep but just missed the placings. Loves this trip and looks a major player while fresh. BAY OF ZEA (16) has been freshened up since opening this prep with a couple of nice runs in Adelaide. Sure to be prominent coming back a level or two.
